\par\pard\plain \qj\ltrch\loch {\f2\fs36\b1\i0 21\~}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 The }{\f0\fs24\b0\i0\scaps Lord}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0  visited Sarah as he had said, and the }{\f0\fs24\b0\i0\scaps Lord}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0  did to Sarah as he had promised. }{\f1\fs24\b1\i0\super 2\~}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 And Sarah conceived and bore Abraham a son in his old age at the time of which God had spoken to him. }{\f1\fs24\b1\i0\super 3\~}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Abraham called the name of his son who was born to him, whom Sarah bore him, Isaac. }{\f1\fs24\b1\i0\super 4\~}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 And Abraham circumcised his son Isaac when he was eight days old, as God had commanded him. }{\f1\fs24\b1\i0\super 5\~}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 Abraham was a hundred years old when his son Isaac was born to him. }{\f1\fs24\b1\i0\super 6\~}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 And Sarah said, \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93God has made laughter for me; everyone who hears will laugh over me.\u8221\'94 }{\f1\fs24\b1\i0\super 7\~}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0 And she said, \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Who would have said to Abraham that Sarah would nurse children? Yet I have borne him a son in his old age.\u8221\'94 \{\\Scrv_fn=}{\f3\fs24\b0\i0  \\end_Scrv_fn\}\{\\Scrv_fn=}{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://ref.ly/logosres/esv?ref=BibleESV.Ge21.1"}{\fldrslt\f4\fs24\b0\i1\ul\ulc0\cf3 The Holy Bible: English Standard Version\\end_Scrv_fn\}\{\\Scrv_fn=}}{\f3\fs24\b0\i0 . (2016). (Ge 21:1\endash 7). Wheaton: Standard Bible Society.\\end_Scrv_fn\}}
